There is no evidence that Propertius left any child behind him; the words ol Pliny do not necessarily mean more than that Passennus counted Propertius as belonging to a previous generation of his family; and even is they do mean more, the claim of Passennus to be descended from Propertius as an ancestor is no more prool of the lact than the similar claim of the emperor Tacitus to be descended from the historian. N evertheless, the statement ol Pliny, taken along with the inscription, raises a strong proba- bility that the Propertii were connected with Asisium, and that Asisium was the nearest important town to the property on which the poet was born .
